race.comment: THREE ARROWS (4) started favourite on debut last start over 1250m here but after leading for home found a couple marginally better in the final stages. The blinkers go on and with that race experience now on board he will be tough to beat. BLAZING FUTURE (1) was friendless in betting but worked through the line impressively to get up for third on debut over 1300m at Hawkesbury last time out. Will appreciate the longer run home at Newcastle and looms as a serious threat. REIGN CAPITAL (9) has not appeared since finishing midfield as favourite on debut over 1200m at Geelong in June. Trialled twice this way of going recently. No surprise if he ran a big race. SO REBELLIOUS (10) was caught wide in the early stages then battled away just fairly when resuming over 1400m at Goulburn recently. Fitter and capable of a top three finish. PERFECT APPLE (7) raced wide without cover so his first-up failure at Rosehill is worth overlooking.
